## Commands

`task` (or `task menu`) shows the interactive picker. Key targets:

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `task verify` | Local merge gate: lint[% if use_node %] + typecheck + build[% endif %] |
| `task check` | All linters in parallel |
| `task fix` | Auto-format, then lint |
[% if use_node %]
| `task dev` | Dev server with hot reload |
| `task build` | Production build |
[% endif %]
| `task test` | Run tests (see [docs/testing.md](docs/testing.md)) |
| `task security` | gitleaks + dependency audit |
| `task release:patch` | Tag + GitHub release (also `:minor` / `:major`) |
| `task status` | Project status dashboard |

## Testing

See [docs/testing.md](docs/testing.md). Tests live in `tests/`; CI runs the
same `task` targets as local hooks.

## CI/CD

| Workflow | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `build.yml` | lint[% if use_node %], build-test[% endif %][% if project_type == 'web-astro' %], lighthouse[% endif %], security → aggregate `verify` gate |
[% if use_node or use_python %]
| `codeql.yml` | CodeQL analysis (opt-in via `FULL_SECURITY_SCAN` repo variable) |
[% endif %]
[% if devcontainer %]
| `devcontainer-build.yml` | Prebuilds devcontainer images to GHCR on merge to main |
[% endif %]
| `claude-plan/implement/review.yml` | `@claude plan` / `@claude implement` / `@claude review` on issues & PRs |

Branch protection: `main` requires a PR with code-owner approval and the
`verify` + `security` checks (importable ruleset in `.github/`; see
[docs/branchProtection.md](docs/branchProtection.md)).

**Releases are intentional** — run `task release:patch|minor|major`; nothing
auto-releases on merge.

